Deputy Speaker of the House of Representatives, Hon. Ahmed Wase has called on Nigerian leaders at all levels to ensure justice and fair play to govern their actions. Hon. Wase gave the charge via a commemorative message issued to mark Nigeria’s 59th Independence Anniversary. In the same vein, the Deputy Speaker in the statement issued by his chief press secretary, Umar Muhammad Puma, urged Nigerians to support the government at all levels, saying the task of nation-building requires the contribution of every citizen. He called on Nigerians to improve the way they relate to one another, adding that there is the urgent need for the people to begin to see themselves first as Nigerians, rather than individual ethnic or sectional groups or the other. Nigeria @ 59: Nigeria will be sitting on time bomb if…… #NigeriaAt59: President Buhari’s Independence Day speech… Kidnappers yet to release wife of railway boss as police… Nigeria@59: 9-year-old Ifeanyichukwu, nine others grab… ALSO READ: FCT Police condemns killing of three suspected one-chance robbers by mob “The future of the country lies in its ability to achieve unity and peace and would be much easier to attain if leaders at all levels allow justice and fair play to govern their actions,” Hon. Wase noted. He stated that when people believe in the fairness of their leaders, they would be ready to do everything within their power to protect their fatherland. The Deputy Speaker while maintaining that the future of the country is bright, appealed to groups that are aggrieved in one way or the other and espousing separatist sentiments, to drop their agitation and take advantage of the improving political climate in the country, to seek accommodation in the larger united national community that is fast unfolding. How premature ejaculation  and small penis almost ruin my marriage and made my wife cheat on me, until my Abuja doctor recommend this powerful but simple solution that work wonder...DONT BE A VICTIM.... SHOCKING LIF